{
  "texts": [
    "During CAG, the operator can record videos which often encompass anatomical structures beyond the RCAs and LCAs, such as the aorta, radial artery, left ventricle, catheter, or femoral artery.",
    "Previously, as part of CathAI's pipeline 5, an Xception image-based model 24 was trained and tested on 14,366 CAG images acquired at the University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) and separated by cardiologists in 11 classes representing primary anatomic structures (listed in Supplementary Table 3) 5.",
    "9887 (70%) of those images were used for training, 1504 (10%) were used for validation and 2975 (20%) were used for testing 5.",
    "A video-level prediction was calculated by determining the most frequent frame-level prediction in a video 5.",
    "This algorithm allowed to detect LCAs and RCAs with PPVs of 97% and 93% respectively on their test set 5."
  ]
}